  "critical": false,
  "description": "Domesticated fowl (Gallus gallus domesticus) raised for eggs and meat. The most widely kept poultry species, producing 200-300 eggs per year for modern layers on just 100-150g feed/day. Dual-purpose breeds provide both eggs and meat, reaching slaughter weight at 12-16 weeks on range.",
  "early_win": true,
  "early_win_note": "Point-of-lay at 18-22 weeks, eggs within first year. Minimal space requirements and efficient feed conversion make chickens the fastest livestock to establish.",
